1.use
	eval("")
  to calculate formula from string directly

2.Use something like
      my_str1 = str(n)
  to convert number n (integer or float) to a string representation.
  
  Use
      my_str2 = "{:.8f}".format(n)
  to convert n to string, with 8 digits after decimal point precision.

3.Suppose ent is an Entry instance
	  ent.configure(state = "normal")
	  [change ent]
	  ent.configure(state = "readonly")
  to set ent to toggle the state of ent between normal and readonly to

4.Use
	global var
  at the beginning of function, to access(set/get) global variable

5.Use
	math.radians(deg)
  to turn degree into radian

6.Error handling: ZeroDivisionError or SyntaxError

7.near-zero values

8.square root


